dcterms:creator: A. Krizhevsky
dcterms:description: CIFAR-10 is a dataset consisting of 60,000 32x32 color images in 10 different classes, with 6,000 images per class. It is commonly used for training machine learning models in image classification tasks.
dcterms:title: CIFAR-10

dcterms:creator: A. Krizhevsky
dcterms:description: CIFAR-100 is a dataset similar to CIFAR-10 but contains 100 classes with 600 images each. It is used for more fine-grained classification tasks.
dcterms:title: CIFAR-100

dcterms:creator: H. Xiao
K. Rasul
R. Vollgraf
dcterms:description: FashionMNIST is a dataset consisting of 70,000 grayscale images of clothing items, designed as a drop-in replacement for the original MNIST dataset for benchmarking machine learning algorithms.
dcterms:title: FashionMNIST

dcterms:creator: O. Russakovsky

dcterms:description: ImageNet is a large visual database designed for use in visual object recognition software research. It contains millions of images across thousands of categories.
dcterms:title: ImageNet

dcterms:creator: R. Geirhos
P. Rubisch
C. Michaelis
M. Bethge
F. A. Wichmann
W. Brendel
dcterms:description: The Geirhos Style-Transfer (GST) dataset is designed for evaluating shape and texture bias in neural networks. It contains images where the shape belongs to one class and the texture to another.
dcterms:title: Geirhos Style-Transfer (GST) Dataset

dcterms:creator: Stanford
dcterms:description: Tiny ImageNet is a smaller version of the ImageNet dataset, containing 200 classes with 500 training images and 50 validation images per class. It is used for visual recognition challenges.
dcterms:title: Tiny ImageNet
